). Epandrium with 11-14 setae on medial to dorsal portion and approximately four setae on ventral lobe (Fig. 2E). Surstylus with 6-7 apically pointed prensisetae arranged along caudobasal margin and 40-42 recurved setae on ventral portion of inner surface (Fig. 2E, F). Cercus nearly entirely pubescent except for lateral to ventral margin, with 21-24 setae (Fig. 2E, F). Hypandrium caudolaterally pubescent and fused to gonopod, with a pair of inward extended plates apically articulated to bases of parameres (Fig. 2G).
